         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">19/3/79 ¶  ¶ I am writing to you this time, dear and learned friend, to ask you whether it lies in your province to see worked up a future collection of longicorn coleoptera, since of course such a tr...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">79.03.19</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Ferdinand von Krauss</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">Staatliches Museum für Naturkunde, Stuttgart.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Krauss: 'Rep. 20. Mai 79 empf. 16. Mai 79'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[Replied 20 May 79. received 16 May 79].<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Krauss's letter not found.</p>
               </note>19/3/79</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich schreibe Ihnen diesmal, theurer u. gelehrter Freund, um Sie zu befragen, ob es in Ihrem Bereiche liegt, eine etwaige Sammlung von Longicornia coleoptera bearbeitet zu sehen, da selbstverständlich eine solche Bearbeitung nur von einem Specialisten vorgenommen<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>werden<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">left out in MS</seg>.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>kann, dem gleichzeitig das nöthige Material zum Vergleich und die bibliothekarischen Mittel zu Gebote stehen. Es ist hier nämlich eine Sammlung von etwa 300 Arten kaufbar, alle australisch, von denen etwa ein hundert neu sein möchten. Es wird aber ein sehr bedeutender Preis (etwa<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>£30<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>£300<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">corrected to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>£30.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>also über 200<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Thaler) dafür gefordert. Vielleicht würde ich auch dies Opfer bringen und Ihnen die Sammlung zuwenden, aber es wäre doch eine zu bedeutende und unverhältnissmässige Ausgabe, wenn man nicht durch die Bekanntmachung von reichlich Neuen (ehe uns jemand zuvor kommt) etwas Ersatz hätte.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Es geht bald wieder allerlei an Sie ab, darunter einige schöne Ex. des Neuseeländisch. Nestor. Aus beigefügtem Briefe werden Sie aber ersehen, dass ein bedeutender Preis für unsere sogenannten Alligatoren bezahlt werden müsste (u. dann kommen noch die bedeutenden Fracht Unkosten bis Stuttgart dazu),<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>(u. dann … dazu)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">is a marginal note with its intended position marked with an asterisk.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>u. da doch die Species wohl nicht vom Ganges Crocodil verschieden ist, so könnte<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>könnten?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>doch Exemplare viel billiger von Indien bezogen werden.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Stets verehrungsvoll</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ihr Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Ich habe mich recht gefreuet über die Zuneigung Seitens Sr. Excell. Staatsrath v. Regels der Gartenflora von 1878, welche ja in Ihrer Stadt erscheint. Den Pastor Dr. Bromby sah ich wohlgemuth vor einigen Tagen.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="line-height: 0.1944in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">19/3/79</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="line-height: 0.1944in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am writing to you this time, dear and learned friend, to ask you whether it lies in your province to see worked up a future collection of longicorn coleoptera, since of course such a treatment can only [be] undertaken by a specialist, to whom the necessary material for comparison and the bibliographical means are available together. There is here a collection of about 300 species available for purchase, all Australian, of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>which about one hundred may be new.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The collection of longicorns was presumably<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Charles French<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Snr; see M to R. Owen, 30 October 1878.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>However, a very considerable price (about<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>£30,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>therefore over 200 Taler) is asked for it. Perhaps I would also make this sacrifice and procure the collection for you, but it would certainly be a very considerable and disproportionate expenditure, if there were<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>not some compensation through the publication of plentiful new things (before anyone anticipates us).<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>French's collection apparently was refused by both Krauss and Owen. In an interview with Charles French published in the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Leader</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(Melbourne), 22 February 1890, p. 38, it was reported that his longicorn beetle collection was in the Leyden Museum.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="line-height: 0.1944in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Soon all kinds of things go off to you again, among<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>them<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>some beautiful specimens of New Zealand<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Nestor</seg>. However, from the enclosed letter<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See F. Kilner to M, 5 March 1879.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>you will see that a considerable price must be paid for our so-called alligator and then in addition still the considerable costs of freight to Stuttgart, and since the species is probably not different from the Ganges crocodile, specimens could be got much cheaper from India.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="line-height: 0.1944in; margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Always respectfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="line-height: 0.1944in; margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="line-height: 0.1944in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0.0555in; "
               xml:lang="en">I am very pleased about the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>affection<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on the part of His Excellency<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>State Counsellor<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>von Regel of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Gartenflora</seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of 1878, which is published in your city.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn8" n="9">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This volume of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Gartenflora</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was dedicated to M with an accompanying dedicatory letter to M by von Regel; see E. von Regel to M, 1878 (in this edition as 78-00-00a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I saw pastor Dr Bromby cheerfully some days ago.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
